<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Waters, G.F. et al. (1992). The role of high-level speech planning in rehearsal: Evidence from patients with apraxia of speech. <i>Journal of Memory and Language</i> 31, 54–73.</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Baddeley, A.D. &amp; Wilson, B.A. (1985). Phonological coding and shortterm memory in patients without speech. <i>Journal of Memory and Language</i> 24, 490–502.</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> Baddeley, A.D. (2000). The episodic buffer: A new component of working memory? <i>Trends in Cognitive Science,</i> 4, 417-423.</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> Logie, R.H.(1995). <i>Visuo-spatial working memory</i>, Hove, UK: Lawrence Eribaum Associates.</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Klauer, K. C., &amp; Zhao, Z. (2004). Double dissociations in visual and spatial short-term memory. Journal of Experimental Psychology: General, 133, 355–381.</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> mentioned in: <a href="http://www.psypress.com/ek5/resources/demo_ch06-sc-02.asp" class="external free" title="http://www.psypress.com/ek5/resources/demo_ch06-sc-02.asp" rel="nofollow">http://www.psypress.com/ek5/resources/demo_ch06-sc-02.asp</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> Smith, E. E., &amp; Jonides, J. (1997).</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Baddeley, A. D., &amp; Wilson, B. A.(2002). Prose recall and amnesia: implications for the structure of working memory. Neuropsychologia, 40, 1737-1743.</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Jones, D. M., Macken, W. J., &amp; Nicholls, A. P. (2004). The phonological store of working memory: is it phonological and is it a store? <i>Journal of Experimental Psychology: Learning, Memory, and Cognition</i>, 30, 656-674.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Nairne, J. S. (2002). Remembering over the short-term: The case against the standard model. <i>Annual Review of Psychology</i>, 53, 53-81.</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.psypress.com/ek5/resources/demo_ch06-sc-02.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.psypress.com/ek5/resources/demo_ch06-sc-02.asp" rel="nofollow">Cognitive Psychology: A Student's Handbook&#160;:: 5th Edition: Chapter Topic</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
